      "content": "# document model structure has metadata specifications and modules\n\nA document model consists of three layers:\n\n1. **Basic Metadata** — `id`, `name`, `extension`, `description`, `author` (name + website)\n2. **Specifications** — Versioned specs containing `version`, `changeLog`, and `state` definitions (global/local with schema, initialValue, examples)\n3. **Modules** — Operational modules that group related operations\n\nThe metadata identifies the model. The specifications define its state shape. The modules organize what operations can be performed on that state.\n\nSince [[document models have 37 available operations across 7 categories]], the operations for building a document model span header setup, module creation, operation definition, and state schema configuration.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[schema design]]",
